3. Compilation & Run Steps

Step 1: Compile
Bash
make

Step 2: Load Module
Bash
sudo insmod mydriver.ko
Check major number:
Bash
dmesg

Step 3: Create Device File
Bash
sudo mknod /dev/mydevice c <major_number> 0
Example:
Bash
sudo mknod /dev/mydevice c 240 0

Step 4: Write to Device
Bash
echo "Hello Kernel" > /dev/mydevice

Step 5: Read from Device
Bash
cat /dev/mydevice

Step 6: Remove Module
Bash
sudo rmmod mydriver

📊 Expected Output

Plain text
Device registered with Major Number: 240
Data received from user: Hello Kernel
Data sent to user
Device unregistered
